The paper addresses the problem of learning hierarchical deep neural network policies for reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of deep neural networks suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on reinforcement learning suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). The use of latent variables and the mention of benchmark tasks suggest that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
